  <body>
    <h2><b>Create HelloWorld Application with OPRoS Component Composer, an OPRoS
        Tool, then distribute the package into robots, and execute the
        application with monitoring</b></h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Click "Component Composer" perspective<br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_01.JPG" height="58" width="501"></li>
      <li>Top menu "Window", select "Preferences". Set "Local Repository Path"
        into <strong>OPRoS\OprosDevelopment\Repository\Components</strong> in
        OPRoS item <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_02.JPG" height="223" width="310"><br>
      </li>
      <li>"Solution" in left, click cross mark for sub contents to see "Package
        Diagram". Then double click it. <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_03.JPG" height="218" width="344"><br>
      </li>
      <li>Clicking "Package" shows Property in lower right corner. Change the
        package name from "Package" to "HelloWorld"<br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_04.JPG" height="217" width="344"><br>
      </li>
      <li>Click "Local Repository" and select refresh from right click, and then
        HelloMaker and MessagePrinter component will be displayed. <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_05.JPG" height="218" width="344"><br>
      </li>
      <li>Click HelloMaker under the "Local Repository" and drag it into the
        painting board.<br>
      </li>
      <li>The same way to MessagePrinter component <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_06.JPG" height="218" width="344"> <br>
      </li>
      <li>Select "Connection" in the palette, right side of the painting board<br>
      </li>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <ul>
        <li>If you don't see the palette, then find a tri-angle in upper right
          corner, and click it</li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <li>Connect from the service port MessagePrint of HelloMaker to the
        service port MessagePrint of MessagePrinter</li>
      <li>Connect form the data port DataOut of HelloMaker to the data port
        DataIn of MessagePrinter <br>
      </li>
      <li>Connect form the event port EventOut of HelloMaker to the event port
        EventIn of MessagePrinter <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_07.JPG" height="220" width="348"><br>
      </li>
      <li>Click "Robots" with right button, then select "Add Robot", and click
        o.k. button <br>
      </li>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <ul>
        <li>The default value is "robot1"</li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <li>Click created "robot1" with right button, then select "Add&nbsp;Node",
        and click o.k. button</li>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <ul>
        <li>The default value is "node1" <br>
          <img alt="" src="../img/cc_08.JPG" height="218" width="344"><br>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <li>Click created "node1" with right button, then select "Get Packages"</li>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <ul>
        <li>Before the selection "Get Package", Component Execution Engine
          should be running</li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <ul>
        <li>Double click run.bat in OPRoS\OprosRobot\Binnary <br>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <li>Click created "node1" and drag it into the center part of each
        components <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_10.JPG" height="209" width="331"><br>
      </li>
      <li>To run component execution engine, double click run.bat file in OPRoS\<strong></strong>OprosRobot\Binary</li>
      <li>At HelloWorld click with right mouse button to choose "Deploy" and
        select "robot1.nod1"</li>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <ul>
        <li>One service can work with multi nodes <br>
          <img alt="" src="../img/cc_11.JPG" height="220" width="347"><br>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
      </ol>
      <li><strong>Repeat #14</strong> to see newly distributed application
        HelloWorld</li>
      <li>Click the application "HelloWorld" with right mouse button to select
        "Run Package" <br>
        <img alt="" src="../img/cc_12.JPG" height="225" width="357"><br>
      </li>
      <li>The Component Engine should be print messages</li>
      <li>To stop the application, click the application with right mouse button
        "HelloWorld" then select "Stop Package" <br>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p>Reference: <a href="http://ropros.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=4161548">A
        simple-to-installation/execution for running OPRoS on Windows</a></p>
  </body>
</html>
